---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="AC Repair & Installation | Comffordable Air Solutions" description="Expert air conditioning repair and high-efficiency installation services in St. Petersburg, Tampa, and Clearwater. Fast emergency service available.">
    <main>
        <section class="hero"
            style="min-height: 60vh; align-items: center;">
            <img src="/images/service 2.png" alt="Professional HVAC technician repairing air conditioning unit" class="hero-bg-img" loading="eager" width="1920" height="1080" />
            <div class="hero-overlay" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.55), rgba(0,0,0,0.75));"></div>
            <div class="container hero-content text-center" style="margin: 0 auto;">
                <h1 style="font-size: 4.5rem; text-shadow: 2px 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.8); margin-bottom: 1rem;">AC Repair &amp; Installation <span class="text-purple">Tampa Bay, FL</span></h1>
                <p
                    style="margin: 0 auto; font-size: 1.5rem; text-shadow: 1px 1px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.8); max-width: 800px;">
                    Fast, reliable cooling solutions for your home.
                    Servicing <a href="/service-areas/st-petersburg-fl" class="text-purple"
                        style="font-weight: 500;">St. Petersburg</a>, <a href="/service-areas/tampa-fl"
                        class="text-purple" style="font-weight: 500;">Tampa</a>, and <a
                        href="/service-areas/clearwater-fl" class="text-purple" style="font-weight: 500;">Clearwater</a>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="process-section" style="padding-top: 4rem;">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="services-grid">

                    <!-- Diagnostic -->
                    <div class="glass-panel service-card animate-on-scroll">
                        <h3>Diagnostic & Repair</h3>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Experiencing issues? Our technicians provide thorough diagnostics to identify and fix leaks, compressor issues, or electrical faults.</p>
                        <ul style="list-style: none; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Multi-point System Inspection</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Refrigerant Leak Detection</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Thermostat Calibration</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Emergency Component Repair</li>
                        </ul>
                        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width: 100%; text-align: center;">Book Now</a>
                    </div>

                    <!-- New Install -->
                    <div class="glass-panel service-card animate-on-scroll"
                        style="transition-delay: 0.2s; border-color: var(--primary-purple); box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(30, 136, 229, 0.4); position: relative;">
                        <h3>System Installation</h3>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Upgrade to a high-efficiency SEER2 certified system. We handle everything from sizing to final ductwork integration.</p>
                        <ul style="list-style: none; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Expert Sizing & Selection</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Professional Full Installation</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Old Unit Disposal Included</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Manufacturer Warranty Protection</li>
                        </ul>
                        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width: 100%; text-align: center; color: white;">Get Free Quote</a>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Commercial -->
                    <div class="glass-panel service-card animate-on-scroll" style="transition-delay: 0.4s;">
                        <h3>Commercial AC</h3>
                        <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Custom solutions for office buildings, retail spaces, and restaurants across the Tampa Bay Area.</p>
                        <ul style="list-style: none; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Large Scale Roof Units</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Custom Duct Layouts</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Industrial Maintenance Plans</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><i class="fa-solid fa-check text-purple"></i> Rapid Business Response</li>
                        </ul>
                        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width: 100%; text-align: center; position: relative;">Consultation</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Add-ons Section -->
        <section>
            <div class="container animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="section-title">
                    <h2>Specialized Air Services</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="glass-panel">
                    <div class="specialized-grid">
                        <!-- Column 1: Emergency -->
                        <div class="animate-on-scroll glass-panel" style="text-align: center; display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: 100%;">
                            <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Emergency Service</h4>
                            <p class="text-secondary" style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                                HVAC failures don't follow a schedule. Our rapid-response repairs prevent your home from reaching dangerous temperatures during the peak Florida heat.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-secondary" style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; background: rgba(30, 136, 229, 0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
                                <strong>How to Detect:</strong> Watch for burning smells, loud grinding noises, or a complete loss of cooling when the sun is at its peak. If your home feels like a sauna, don't wait.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-purple" style="font-style: italic; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; flex: 1;">
                                Comfort isn't just a luxury—it's your home's cool superpower, so keep it charged!
                            </p>
                            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width: 100%; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;">CALL FOR QUOTE</a>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Column 2: Smart + UV Stacked -->
                        <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem;">
                            <div class="animate-on-scroll glass-panel" style="text-align: center; display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: 100%; transition-delay: 0.1s;">
                                <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Smart Thermostats</h4>
                                <p class="text-secondary" style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; flex: 1;">
                                    Modernize your home with Ecobee or Nest integration. These systems learn your habits to optimize cooling cycles and allow for remote climate management.
                                </p>
                                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width: 100%; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;">CALL FOR QUOTE</a>
                            </div>
                            <div class="animate-on-scroll glass-panel" style="text-align: center; display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: 100%; transition-delay: 0.3s;">
                                <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">UV Filter Install</h4>
                                <p class="text-secondary" style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; flex: 1;">
                                    We install medical-grade UV-C light systems directly into your air handler to neutralize mold, bacteria, and airborne viruses before they circulate.
                                </p>
                                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width: 100%; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;">CALL FOR QUOTE</a>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <!-- Column 3: Duct Sealing -->
                        <div class="animate-on-scroll glass-panel" style="text-align: center; display: flex; flex-direction: column; height: 100%; transition-delay: 0.2s;">
                            <h4 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Duct Sealing</h4>
                            <p class="text-secondary" style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                                Our precision sealing identifies and repairs leaks in your ductwork where expensive cold air often escapes into your attic space.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-secondary" style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; background: rgba(30, 136, 229, 0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
                                <strong>How to Detect:</strong> Look for uneven cooling between rooms, excessive dust buildup near supply vents, or unexplained spikes in your monthly electric bill.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-purple" style="font-style: italic; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; flex: 1;">
                                Don't let your conditioned air sneak out the back door; keep the cool where it belongs!
                            </p>
                            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width: 100%; text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem;">CALL FOR QUOTE</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--bg-dark), var(--bg-darker)); border-top: 1px solid var(--glass-border); padding: 5rem 0;">
            <div class="container animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="section-title">
                    <span>Florida's Unique Challenge</span>
                    <h2>Why Florida Homes Need Expert AC Repair</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="glass-panel" style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--text-secondary);">
                    <p>In Florida, your air conditioner is not a seasonal appliance. It is the most critical piece of infrastructure in your home, running nearly every day of the year. The Tampa Bay Area's combination of intense heat, relentless humidity, and sudden afternoon thunderstorms puts mechanical stress on HVAC systems that homeowners in other states simply never experience. A system that lasts 15 years in the Midwest may start failing within 8 to 10 years here, especially without regular maintenance.</p>
                    <p>Salt air from Tampa Bay's coastal zones accelerates corrosion on condenser coils and electrical components, causing refrigerant leaks and compressor failures at a higher rate than inland markets. High humidity also creates condensation inside air handlers, leading to clogged drain lines, one of the leading causes of water damage in Florida homes. Our technicians are trained specifically for these conditions and know which failure points to inspect first, cutting diagnostic time and getting your system back online faster.</p>
                    <p>Beyond breakdowns, an improperly sized or maintained system in Florida costs you money every single month. Undersized units run constantly and never dehumidify properly, leaving your home feeling sticky at 72 degrees. Oversized units short-cycle, creating uneven temperature zones and excess moisture. Our certified technicians provide load calculations, refrigerant checks, and full system evaluations to make sure your AC is genuinely matched to your home, not just patched together for the next few months. Get <a href="/maintenance" class="text-purple" style="font-weight:600;">proactive care</a> before the next breakdown finds you first.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">

            <div class="container">
                <div style="height: 1100px"><iframe src="https://www.localmarketingmanager.com/api/questions/comffordable-air-solutions-frequently-asked-questions?textColor=%23000000&backgroundColor=%23ffffff&showTitle=true&borderRadius=10px&visibility=showAllExpanded&isTransparentBackgroundApplied=false" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; border: none;" loading="lazy" id="ai-seo-iframe"></iframe></div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
